name: media_png_invalid_truncated_zlib_stream
description: |
  A deliberately invalid PNG whose IDAT chunk has a correct PNG chunk CRC, but
  the zlib stream inside IDAT is truncated. This separates PNG chunk integrity
  from compressed image-data integrity: a parser that only checks chunk CRCs
  still has to surface the decompression failure.

  This file is independently constructed for this corpus and is MIT licensed.
  The PNG specification requires compression method 0 to use zlib/deflate:
  https://www.w3.org/TR/png-3/#10Compression
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
mime-type: image/png
licence: MIT
pair:
  - with: valid-minimal-rgba-1x1.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "media"
  - "image"
  - "png"
  - "invalid-png"
  - "idat"
  - "zlib"
  - "truncated"
---
89 50 4e 47 0d 0a 1a 0a
00 00 00 0d 49 48 44 52 00 00 00 01 00 00 00 01 08 06 00 00 00 1f 15 c4 89
00 00 00 08 49 44 41 54 78 da 63 60 00 02 00 00 8a 98 55 7e
00 00 00 00 49 45 4e 44 ae 42 60 82
